args:
The prince can't believe Zethia dispelled the
barrier, so Zethia attempts to explain. However,
an otherworld gate suddenly appears and
swallows her up. Despite the prince being
crestfallen, Nedrick and Jinlorda continue on
to the upper strata.
(Surely this final prayer must be the one\nthat dispels the barrier...)
I clearly underestimated the power of the\nIlian Auspex.
The path is open at last. Now we climb the\nCloudbough and make for the upper strata.
Zethia. Valyx. The two of you will\naccompany me as promised.
Zethia is our guest of honor; there was\nnever any risk of her coming to harm.
Why, just now the barrier was taken down\nthanks to her cooperation.
Liar! Zethia would never help you!
Zethia, why?! Why would you help them?!\nWhat did they do to you?!
Calm yourself, Brother. Zethia made this\nchoice of her own free will.
Please, let me explain. My consciousness\nwas transported to an ancient era.
Once there, I witnessed unbelievable\nthingsâ€”a past history completely unlike\nany which we had been taught.
And while I do not trust Nedrick entirely,\nI must learn the truth of this world.
This is why I chose to dispel the barrier.
Remember your promise, Nedrick. Tell my\nbrother what you have learned, and listen\nto what he has to say.
Zethia, get off the altar! Now!
She vanished... No! This isn't happening!
There remains no trace of her.
This was not my doing. I swear I intended\nto release her to you unharmed.
That was most likely an otherworld gate,\nmeaning a third party has stolen her away.
While I have some concern regarding the\npoor woman's current whereabouts,\nI fear we must be off.
With Zethia gone, the barrier has returned.
Fortunate, we had already cleared it.\nCome, Nedrick. We must away.
I am sorry I could not protect our sister.\nI...I will wait for you at the summit.
Do whatever you must to dispel this barrier\nand continue your climb.

Nedrick swore to tell you the truth and
hear your response. He swore it to Zethia,
and he will make good on it or answer
to me.
